        "# GeoGebra Tasks 08 08_Second_Order_Surfaces\n",
        "\n",
        "## 1. Equation of the Sphere with Center at P(1, 2, 3) and Radius r = 3:\n",
        "P = (1, 2, 3)\n",
        "r = 3\n",
        "Equation of the sphere:\n",
        "\\[(x - 1)^2 + (y - 2)^2 + (z - 3)^2 = 9\\]\n",
        "\n",
        "## 2. Do the Spheres with Equations x² + y² + z² = 1 and x² + y² + z² = 2 Have Any Common Points?\n",
        "Spheres:\n",
        "Sphere 1: \\(x^2 + y^2 + z^2 = 1\\)\n",
        "Sphere 2: \\(x^2 + y^2 + z^2 = 2\\)\n",
        "Since the radii are different (1 and √2), the spheres do not intersect at any point.\n",
        "\n",
        "## 3. Curve Formed by the Intersection of the Spheres x² + y² + z² = 1 and (x - 1)² + y² + z² = 1:\n",
        "Spheres:\n",
        "Sphere 1: \\(x^2 + y^2 + z^2 = 1\\)\n",
        "Sphere 2: \\((x - 1)^2 + y^2 + z^2 = 1\\)\n",
        "Solve for the intersection of the two spheres to find the equation of the curve.\n",
        "\n",
        "The equation of the curve formed by the intersection is:\n",
        "\\[ x = \\frac{1}{2}, \\quad y^2 + z^2 = \\frac{3}{4} \\]\n",
        "\n",
        "## 4. Equation of the Tangent Plane to the Paraboloid \\(z = (x - 1)^2 + y^2 + 1\\) at Point P(1, 0, 1):\n",
        "Paraboloid: \\(z = (x - 1)^2 + y^2 + 1\\)\n",
        "Point P = (1, 0, 1)\n",
        "The gradient of the function \\(f(x, y, z) = (x - 1)^2 + y^2 + 1 - z\\) gives the normal vector.\n",
        "Gradient: \\(\\nabla f = (2(x - 1), 2y, -1)\\)\n",
        "At point P(1, 0, 1), the normal vector is \\((0, 0, -1)\\).\n",
        "Equation of the tangent plane:\n",
        "\\[(x - 1)(0) + (y - 0)(0) + (z - 1)(-1) = 0\\]\n",
        "Simplifies to:\n",
        "\\[-(z - 1) = 0 \\quad \\text{or} \\quad z = 1\\]\n"
      ],
